div.p:
Let me give you a sense of our direction by discussing briefly four major points
                    in our approach: 

First, our insistence on restraint and reciprocity in East-West
                            relations;

Second, our determination to strengthen our alliances, particularly
                            the Atlantic alliance;

Third, our intention to play a constructive role in the Third World;
                            and

Fourth, our firm resolve to strengthen our economy and our
                            defenses.
